# ITU BLG102 - Introduction to Scientific and Engineering Computing (C)

This repository contains coursework, assignments, and projects for the **BLG 102 - Introduction to Scientific and Engineering Computing** course at Istanbul Technical University (ITU). The course focuses on problem-solving and algorithmic thinking using the C programming language.

## Contents
- **Assignments:** Exercises covering fundamental programming concepts in C.
- **Projects:** More comprehensive applications demonstrating problem-solving in scientific and engineering contexts.
- **Lecture Notes & Examples:** Additional materials to reinforce key concepts.

## Topics Covered
- Basics of C Programming (Variables, Data Types, Operators)
- Control Flow (Conditionals, Loops)
- Functions and Recursion
- Arrays and Pointers
- File Handling
- Numerical Methods in C
- Data Structures (Basic Implementations)

## Setup & Usage
To compile and run the C programs in this repository, use the following commands:

```sh
# Compile the program
gcc -o main main.c

# Run the program
./main
```

## Notes
- The code follows best practices for structured programming in C.
- No external libraries are used unless explicitly stated.
- Academic integrity is maintained throughout the repository.

